        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2421702169" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7327484818190480012">It&apos;s one of those books in which:<br/><br/>- women get raped, kidnapped, tortured and murdered. Their roles are limited to being victims and past/present love interests;<br/><br/>- the MC is depressed (because his wife and daughter are - guess what! - dead) and uses it as an excuse to be an a**hole but in the end he gets to play superhero.<br/><br/>I didn&apos;t really mind the maggots and flies - if I can&apos;t see them, they&apos;re not disgusting. But it&apos;s just not a good novel. When the murderer was revealed my only reaction was laugh</span>
  <span id="freeText7327484818190480012" style="display:none">It's one of those books in which:<br /><br />- women get raped, kidnapped, tortured and murdered. Their roles are limited to being victims and past/present love interests;<br /><br />- the MC is depressed (because his wife and daughter are - guess what! - dead) and uses it as an excuse to be an a**hole but in the end he gets to play superhero.<br /><br />I didn't really mind the maggots and flies - if I can't see them, they're not disgusting. But it's just not a good novel. When the murderer was revealed my only reaction was laughter because it was so predictable and absurd. Honestly, it's the kind of a plot twist that happens in soap operas and while I was thinking that "hey, at least it'll be amusing if it happens" as I was reading the novel, when it actually did happen... My laughter bitter, not amused. </span>
