<div id="review_1689713305" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1689713305" />
    <a title="Pamela Mclaren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12623232-pamela-mclaren"><img alt="Pamela Mclaren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1586956653p2/12623232.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1689713305?book_show_action=true">Oct 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pamela Mclaren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pamela Mclaren" href="/user/show/12623232-pamela-mclaren">Pamela Mclaren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780553817492" href="/book/show/1019896.The_Chemistry_of_Death">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=mysteries">mysteries</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=from-janice">from-janice</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1689713305" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17910404903412030495">I was hooked from the moment I began reading this book and was compelled to keep reading to the very end. It is that interesting a story.<br/><br/>David Hunter, a former forensic anthropologist fleeing London after the death of his wife and daughter in a DUI driving accident, arrives in the village of Manham and settles in as a partner in a medical practice with a doctor whose own wife had died in an accident. Everything seems to be fine until a body is found by two young boys. Slowly, police become aware</span>
  <span id="freeText17910404903412030495" style="display:none">I was hooked from the moment I began reading this book and was compelled to keep reading to the very end. It is that interesting a story.<br /><br />David Hunter, a former forensic anthropologist fleeing London after the death of his wife and daughter in a DUI driving accident, arrives in the village of Manham and settles in as a partner in a medical practice with a doctor whose own wife had died in an accident. Everything seems to be fine until a body is found by two young boys. Slowly, police become aware of Hunter's former career and expertise, but he continues to be desperate to remain uninvolved ... but by not being open about it, there is almost immediate suspicion by the villagers. <br /><br />Soon the ugliness of rumors bring out the worst in the villagers. While the police struggle to come up with suspects and clues to at the why, a dour religious leader decides to grab the spotlight and thing get even more tense and complex.<br /><br />And the complexity of this story, the complexity of the characters that makes it an ultimate must read. Definitely I'm hooked and I can't wait to read other books by this author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17910404903412030495" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


