<div id="review_4229742" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4229742" />
    <a title="LJ" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/250195-lj"><img alt="LJ" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1436467895p2/250195.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4229742?book_show_action=true">Aug 07, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LJ" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LJ" href="/user/show/250195-lj">LJ</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780593055212" href="/book/show/1328722.The_Chemistry_of_Death">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=police_procedural">police_procedural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=male_author">male_author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=contemporary_post_1945">contemporary_post_1945</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/250195-lj?shelf=england">england</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4229742" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10621086197270835174">THE CHEMISTRY OF DEATH (Suspense-Dr. David Hunter-England-Cont) – Okay<br/>Beckett, Simon – 1st book<br/>Bantam Press, 2006, UK Hardcover – ISBN: 0593055217<br/>First Sentence: A human body starts to decompose four minutes after death.<br/>*** Dr. David Hunter has come to a small town after answering an ad to assist in the practice of the town’s current GP. When the woman’s mutilated body is found, Hunter’s past is also found out. Hunter was once a high-profile forensic anthropologist. When another woman disappears</span>
  <span id="freeText10621086197270835174" style="display:none">THE CHEMISTRY OF DEATH (Suspense-Dr. David Hunter-England-Cont) – Okay<br />Beckett, Simon – 1st book<br />Bantam Press, 2006, UK Hardcover – ISBN: 0593055217<br />First Sentence: A human body starts to decompose four minutes after death.<br />*** Dr. David Hunter has come to a small town after answering an ad to assist in the practice of the town’s current GP. When the woman’s mutilated body is found, Hunter’s past is also found out. Hunter was once a high-profile forensic anthropologist. When another woman disappears, Hunter overcomes his hesitation to help the police but his secrecy leads the town to be suspicious. A third woman disappears; can Hunter find the killer in time to save her life?<br />*** This could have been a very good book, but it wasn’t. Where was this author’s editor? The story was peppered with “had I but known” portents that were distracting and did nothing to enhance or propel the story. The beginning reminded me of Jefferson Bass, but not as well done. I also had a problem with the common premise of the lead character still recovering from the loss of a loved one but fall in love almost immediately. There were some interesting characters in the story and, although it did move a bit slowly at times, that was offset by scenes with suspense so it wasn’t an awful book. Hopefully, the author will improve with his next book but I’ll wait to read it in paperback.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10621086197270835174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


