<div id="review_859684480" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/859684480" />
    <a title="Pfauzgrot S" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5494013-pfauzgrot-s"><img alt="Pfauzgrot S" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1580254543p2/5494013.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/859684480?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pfauzgrot S" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pfauzgrot S" href="/user/show/5494013-pfauzgrot-s">Pfauzgrot S</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer859684480" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5517242054232695224">I have the feeling I already read this exact same story about 20 times. Middle-aged man has retired from being a cop, journalist, medical examiner, etc , after a trauma -usually dead wife and/or child - when suddenly people start dying. As he is drawn into the investigation someone close to him disappears. Gee, giant surprise there. And then it&apos;s all about elaborate ways in which the killer tortures the new girlfriend. whatever. But particularly annoying about this one is that the reason for why</span>
  <span id="freeText5517242054232695224" style="display:none">I have the feeling I already read this exact same story about 20 times. Middle-aged man has retired from being a cop, journalist, medical examiner, etc , after a trauma -usually dead wife and/or child - when suddenly people start dying. As he is drawn into the investigation someone close to him disappears. Gee, giant surprise there. And then it's all about elaborate ways in which the killer tortures the new girlfriend. whatever. But particularly annoying about this one is that the reason for why the killer turned into a killer is so stupid and not credible that I actually rolled my eyes. <br />So I continue my search for good UK mysteries/thrillers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5517242054232695224" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
